caption: Best Mexican street tacos on island! The shells are perfectly made and the meat ans consome is super flavorful. My mouth is watering for more!

LOVE this fusion idea. Vietnamese Birria (steak stew)! We loved the banh mi and the traditional tacos. Flavor was unique and complex. Highly recommend. Gotta dip in the consome for the full experience!

Checked this place out because I was missing Mexican food from my trips to Puerto Vallarta and the pictures looked good on Yelp when I checked them out. It was an interesting experience that was just okay in my book.  Got the combination plate that featured the two Quesatacos and Vampiro with a side of Consume. The flavor of the Birria was very good, but somehow everything seemed to greasy and honestly the presentation wasn't all that with very minimal toppings of onions and cilantro that made it seem like they didn't even try dress the order.  I got a Horchata to drink, but was very irritated when they immediately made it and then asked me after the fact if I wanted to drink it then and there before my order which didn't get completed for another 15 minutes or so.  I get it that some people like to drink their drinks while they wait, but don't make it and then ask. It got watered down with the ice melting because of my wait.  Despite my complaining, it really isn't the place you should judge them on their service as it was only takeout at the time I went there due to COVID-19 business restrictions. I would like to go back, not for their Mexican food, but for their Vietnamese twist using the Birria for their Pho and Bahn Mi. Next time I will make sure to tell them in advance not to make my drink until my order is ready.
Delicious birra tacos. Beef was tasty and tender.
Fascinating fusion. The birria meat is tender and full of flavor. Definitely adding this to the taco Tuesday rotation.

Amazing combination of Mexican birria tacos with pho broth. The tacos are tasty AF and the pho broth is a fantastic complement for these perfectly flash fried beef tacos.  The owner operators have that kind, friendly vibe and are good people. Definitely worth a visit if you’re looking for tasty tacos downtown.

Incredible fusion of authentic Mexican and Vietnamese cuisine. Customer service and overall friendliness was unbeatable. We are fortunate to have these young entrepreneurs serving up such delish food and aloha.
Awesome food, full of flavor. Love the tacos and banh mi, can’t wait to try their pho next!!

This stuff is delicious! We bought the Bahn MI sandwich and the combination plate. It was more than enough for us. I thought the consume for dipping worked better with the bread in the sandwich than the crisp tortilla in the tacos.  The birria meat has a full meaty flavor in wet, tender shreds. I think it is beef. I wish there was enough of a market for kid/goat meat, which is delicious and hard to find.
Great Tacos and Banh Mi!  Spicy salsa was hot but super tasty.  Consomme dipping sauce sooo good!  You gotta give this place a try.  I'll be back
